279
00:28:44.014 --> 00:28:47.684
This beach boy will catch
rays all daylong.

280
00:28:51.021 --> 00:28:53.273
He's not aware that
soon he'll play

281
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:56.735
an important part in
Bunji's epic odyssey.

282
00:29:03.825 --> 00:29:06.787
As for Bunji. time is ticking.

283
00:29:06.954 --> 00:29:09.581
She must get ready
for her big day.

284
00:29:09.873 --> 00:29:13.085
but first she has to
make a quick stop.

285
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.589
Over 100 different
species can be found

286
00:29:17.756 --> 00:29:20.300
living on green sea turtles.

287
00:29:21.551 --> 00:29:24.554
The parasites help keep
her camouflaged

288
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:28.850
but they also slow her down and
can be quite itchy.

289
00:29:29.768 --> 00:29:31.979
It's time to get some off.

290
00:29:32.145 --> 00:29:36.066
but how do you do that with
flippers for fingers?

291
00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:41.738
She's looking for
something special.

292
00:29:42.155 --> 00:29:45.284
The right spot with the
right sort of fish.

293
00:29:46.702 --> 00:29:48.745
These parrotfish are too big.

294
00:29:49.788 --> 00:29:52.916
and these chromis fish
are too small.

295
00:29:54.751 --> 00:29:59.423
Ah. but these tangs
are just right.

296
00:30:00.716 --> 00:30:03.927
Bunji has found a
cleaning station.

297
00:30:04.970 --> 00:30:08.015
It's a place where smaller fish
feed off the creatures

298
00:30:08.181 --> 00:30:10.684
living on larger animals.

299
00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:15.188
This is known as a
symbiotic relationship.

300
00:30:16.398 --> 00:30:18.025
It's win-win.

301
00:30:19.151 --> 00:30:21.236
The little fish get fed.

302
00:30:21.403 --> 00:30:24.114
and the larger animals like
Bunji get cleaned.

303
00:30:24.281 --> 00:30:26.116
Everybody's happy.

304
00:30:26.867 --> 00:30:30.704
And with a shell as sensitive as
a human fingertip.

305
00:30:30.871 --> 00:30:33.373
she also likes a good scratch.

306
00:30:33.999 --> 00:30:35.876
and a scratch.

307
00:30:37.544 --> 00:30:39.046
and a scratch.

308
00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:47.512
But Bunji's not the only one who
likes a good scrub.

309
00:30:48.597 --> 00:30:52.267
A squadron of rays is about
to hit the station.

310
00:30:56.563 --> 00:30:59.691
These bad boys can
have a wingspan

311
00:30:59.858 --> 00:31:00.901
of over twenty feet.

312
00:31:01.068 --> 00:31:04.529
and weigh up to 3.000 pounds.

313
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:08.700
That's the same as an
average family car.

314
00:31:11.787 --> 00:31:13.622
So when these guys arrive.

315
00:31:13.789 --> 00:31:16.458
they go right to
the front of the line.

316
00:31:18.460 --> 00:31:22.214
And that means smaller fish.
like this batfish.

317
00:31:22.631 --> 00:31:24.174
get bumped to the back.

318
00:31:26.510 --> 00:31:28.011
Because in nature.

319
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:31.223
size really does matter.

320
00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:41.441
But Bunji doesn't have
time to wait.

321
00:31:42.401 --> 00:31:44.069
As the currents pick up.

322
00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:47.280
she's being called to her
final destination.

323
00:31:48.907 --> 00:31:52.202
But forces of nature are
rising against her.

324
00:32:11.012 --> 00:32:12.556
Bunji struggles.

325
00:32:15.642 --> 00:32:20.063
Even below the waves. the
currents swirl around her.

326
00:32:20.772 --> 00:32:22.149
With low visibility.

327
00:32:22.315 --> 00:32:24.609
Bunji is using an
invisible force

328
00:32:24.776 --> 00:32:27.279
to guide her to a very
special place.

329
00:32:37.456 --> 00:32:40.125
Bunji's brain can
actually detect

330
00:32:40.292 --> 00:32:43.128
the magnetic fields
of the earth.

331
00:32:46.631 --> 00:32:51.803
Every place on the globe has a
unique magnetic fingerprint.

332
00:32:52.637 --> 00:32:56.349
Bunji uses this
information like a map.

333
00:32:56.850 --> 00:33:00.145
As she gets close. her
map matches that

334
00:33:00.312 --> 00:33:02.647
of her current location.

335
00:33:03.148 --> 00:33:04.649
At last.

336
00:33:05.567 --> 00:33:07.777
she's reached her destination.

337
00:33:16.328 --> 00:33:17.913
She's home.

338
00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:23.752
After 25 years at sea.

339
00:33:23.919 --> 00:33:27.297
she's come back to the very
beach she was born on.

340
00:33:45.649 --> 00:33:47.526
And she's not alone.

341
00:33:58.620 --> 00:34:00.497
The Great Barrier Reef is
host to the biggest

342
00:34:00.664 --> 00:34:04.167
green sea turtle
rookery in the world.

343
00:34:14.302 --> 00:34:17.222
Bunji's big adventure
is one shared

344
00:34:17.389 --> 00:34:19.307
by thousands of other turtles.

345
00:34:21.017 --> 00:34:22.477
All around the world.

346
00:34:22.644 --> 00:34:26.189
green sea turtles are making
similar great migrations

347
00:34:26.356 --> 00:34:28.775
to the beaches where
they were born.

348
00:34:32.028 --> 00:34:34.906
So. this family of turtles

349
00:34:35.073 --> 00:34:37.325
may have been coming back to
this very beach.

350
00:34:37.492 --> 00:34:39.244
generation after generation.

351
00:34:39.369 --> 00:34:41.621
for thousands of years.

352
00:34:44.332 --> 00:34:48.878
It's one of nature's most
astonishing family reunions.

353
00:34:50.005 --> 00:34:52.799
Now it's Bunji's turn
to play her part

354
00:34:52.966 --> 00:34:55.552
in that larger turtle story.

355
00:34:56.928 --> 00:35:00.390
It's time for Bunji
to find a boyfriend.

356
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:34.674
Once Bunji has mated.

357
00:35:34.841 --> 00:35:38.386
she will remain close to shore
for over a month.

358
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:46.144
Then. when the time is right.

359
00:35:46.311 --> 00:35:48.938
she'll undertake her most
important task.

360
00:35:51.900 --> 00:35:55.737
It's time for Bunji to leave
her water world.

361
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:03.453
It will be her toughest
turtle trial.

362
00:36:04.704 --> 00:36:07.624
After a lifetime of
weightlessness in the ocean.

363
00:36:07.832 --> 00:36:10.418
gravity really sucks.

364
00:36:13.046 --> 00:36:15.632
Weighing in at 250 pounds.

365
00:36:15.799 --> 00:36:17.926
Bunji has to
struggle up the same

366
00:36:18.093 --> 00:36:20.261
strip of beach that.
decades before.

367
00:36:20.428 --> 00:36:22.347
she scurried down.

368
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:30.438
She'll spend the next few hours

369
00:36:30.605 --> 00:36:32.315
digging herself into the sand.

370
00:36:32.482 --> 00:36:34.776
and scooping out a
chamber for her eggs.

371
00:36:35.610 --> 00:36:38.279
It's exhausting work for this
soon-to-be-mother.

372
00:36:38.446 --> 00:36:42.367
but her instinct is unflagging.

373
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:57.799
She'll bury her eggs in
the same sand

374
00:36:57.966 --> 00:37:01.302
her mother did over
25 years ago.

375
00:37:12.105 --> 00:37:14.065
The warm sand will
keep them safe

376
00:37:14.232 --> 00:37:16.192
for the next two
or three months.

377
00:37:25.285 --> 00:37:29.122
Finally. she covers her nest
with the gentle care

378
00:37:29.289 --> 00:37:31.249
that only a mother can give.

379
00:37:39.048 --> 00:37:42.510
Laying five or so clutches
every few years.

380
00:37:45.764 --> 00:37:50.852
she will produce thousands of
offspring in her lifetime.

381
00:38:16.002 --> 00:38:17.420
After along night.

382
00:38:17.712 --> 00:38:20.215
she'll return to the
comfort of the sea.

383
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.970
She'll be back.

384
00:38:26.137 --> 00:38:27.305
but for now.

385
00:38:29.682 --> 00:38:32.936
her odyssey is complete.

386
